description: Before the final act of the nation's electoral drama unfolds and two weeks before Gujarat's inaugural ballot, the state has already dispatched a representative to the Lok Sabha. Mukesh Dalal, the BJP candidate, was announced on Monday as the uncontested victor from Surat, as all eight other contenders withdrew from the race following the rejection of Nilesh Kumbhani, the Congress nominee's nomination the day prior.

description: Congress called upon the Election Commission to halt the Surat elections, claiming that the BJP orchestrated a "match fixing" due to apprehensions about the "furious resentment of small business proprietors." Rahul Gandhi remarked that the uncontested triumph of the BJP in Surat has unmasked the "autocrat's true visage," emphasizing that the 2024 election is pivotal for safeguarding Ambedkar's Constitution.

description: Continuing from his previous remarks in Banswara, Rajasthan, PM Modi criticized the Congress for advocating the "Maoist plan" aimed at wealth redistribution. However, he refrained from explicitly suggesting that Muslims might be the primary beneficiaries of such a scheme. The fresh attack coincided with Congress’s claim that PM had lied about their manifesto. Modi, however, stuck to his guns referring to the manifesto and Rahul’s speeches.

description: Congress lodged a complaint with the Election Commission on Monday, alleging that PM Modi aimed to incite discord between religious communities and spread false information to tarnish the image of the opposition party. They demanded the PM's "disqualification" for serious breaches of election laws in his speech delivered in Rajasthan on Sunday.

This marked the inaugural significant display of unity among all three coalition partners in support of Congress' Balwant Wankhade against BJP's Navneet Rana.

description: A Delhi court on Monday rejected Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal's plea for a video conference consultation with a private doctor. If BJP files a PIL, they get bail; if others file a PIL, it is jail.”

The former NRI doctor, now in politics, submitted his candidacy. Originally from Burripalem in Guntur district, Dr. Sekhar's family roots lie there. His father relocated to Narasaraopet, managing a hotel. Sekhar, securing the 27th position in EAMCET, pursued his MBBS at Osmania University before furthering his studies in the US.

Chidambaram's assertion that the Citizenship (Amendment) Act 2019 (CAA) and the three recent criminal laws would be repealed if Congress were to assume power, labeling it as blatant appeasement. Officials suspect the incident happened on Saturday evening. This situation presents challenges for locals who usually migrate to nearly a dozen high-altitude villages in the Johar valley of the district as the summer season begins.

description: Supreme Court allows 14-year-old rape survivor's pregnancy termination under Article 142. LTMGH's dean supervises, overturning Bombay HC. Sion Hospital to advise post-April 19 examination.
title: SC allows 14-year-old rape survivor to undergo abortion

description: The day after the RCB's defeat in the match against KKR, in which Rajat Patidar smashed a valiant 52 off just 23 balls, RCB showcased the middle-order batsman in a video feature, where the 30-year-old batsman from Madhya Pradesh relived his journey with RCB and beyond, recalling the message Virat Kohli sent after RCB signed him in 2022.
title: Watch: 'Virat Kohli bhaiya ka message aaya, bas ho gaya'

description: CSK's MS Dhoni's grand entrance at Ekana Cricket Stadium during IPL was electrifying. Sasha's Instagram story highlighted the Apple Watch's Noise app measuring sound levels. This feature is available on watchOS 6 and Apple Watch Series 4.
title: Explained: 'Sound warning' that Quinton’s wife shared in CSK vs LSG match

description: The heightened focus on national security is part of Xi's strategy to emphasize external threats, which some analysts view as a tactic to deflect domestic criticism over his policies. This approach has included expanding the definition of espionage within China's counterespionage law, creating a more extensive scope that can affect ordinary business activities and increase surveillance within the country.
title: Under Xi, China's spy agency sees foreign threats ‘everywhere’

description: Punjab Kings are struggling in the IPL 2024 season, with a string of defeats and a narrow three-wicket loss to Gujarat Titans. The defeat marked Punjab's fourth consecutive loss, and stand-in skipper and all-rounder Sam Curran's performances have failed to impress, leaving the franchise in ninth place in the standings.
title: 'I would not even pick him': Sehwag slams Punjab's Curran

description: In Belagavi, Karnataka, a couple coerced a woman with intimate photos into converting to Islam. An FIR was filed against Rafik and his wife for various offenses. The case involves coercion, blackmail, and threats.
title: 28-yr-old woman blackmailed with 'private pics', forced to convert

description: Former Indian spinner Harbhajan Singh expressed reservations about the Decision Review System (DRS), doubting its accuracy in judging bounce. On the 180 Not Out podcast, he questioned DRS's inconsistency, citing discrepancies with cricket's basic principles. Harbhajan criticized umpires' decisions against DRS evidence, advocating for its proper use. In contrast, S Sreesanth supported technology cautiously, advising against complete dependence.
title: 'Aap technology ko...': Ex-India players not 'convinced' with DRS

description: A 58-year-old teacher from Kathlal faces charges of bigamy, domestic violence, and criminal intimidation after allegedly assaulting and abandoning his two wives for a live-in partner.
title: Man remarries for male heir, abandons wives for live-in partner

description: Prohibitory orders in Sangli, Satara due to severe water scarcity. Tankers deployed for 1,060 hamlets without drinking water. Water from dams released into canals. Fodder stock planned for livestock in Atpadi, Jat tehsils.
title: Water crisis: Prohibitory orders in Sangli & Satara districts

description: Empty chairs for Kejriwal and Soren at rally. Sunita accuses Modi govt of plotting husband's death. Opposition unites to save Constitution. BJP predicted to win less than 20 seats in first voting phase.
title: Their chairs empty, jailed Kejriwal, Hemant's voices echo at rally

description: Annapoorani Rajkumar made history as the first woman trucker to cross from Petrapole to Bangladesh, driving from Tamil Nadu with cotton yarn. She faced challenges but received special treatment, highlighting efforts to address gender bias for women truckers.
title: Customs broken, woman drives truck from TN to Bangladesh

description: NIA conducts raids in Srinagar on terrorism suspects associated with TRF, a LeT offshoot. Chargesheet filed in Kokernag case. LeT active in Anantnag, reviving network in Jammu and Kashmir through TRF.
title: NIA conduct raids at several locations in J&K's Srinagar

description: Passengers on a private bus escaped a fire on Mumbai-Pune Expressway after drivers warned them. Despite luggage loss, everyone exited safely. Fire was controlled by brigades, causing travel delays. The incident took place near Dheku village.
title: Lucky escape for 35 as bus goes up in flames at night

description: Hingoli Lok Sabha sees direct fight between Kohalikar and Ashtikar. Ashtikar loyal to Thackeray, faces challenges from Vanchit Bahujan Aghadi's D B Chavan. Prakash Ambedkar leads VBA in a tough election battle.
title: After squaring off in 2019, Sena rivals gear up for clash

description: Around 65,960 Indians have become US citizens, making India the second-largest source country for new citizens in America after Mexico. Additionally, 42% of Indian-born nationals in the US are currently ineligible to become US citizens. 46 million foreign-born people lived in the United States in 2022, accounting for around 14% of the overall population of 333 million.
title: India becomes 2nd largest source for new citizens in US: CSR

description: Rajasthan Royals have been successful in their campaign, with a strong middle-order performance. Jos Buttler, Sanju Samson, and Riyan Parag contributed to most runs, while Caribbean duo Shimron Hetmyer and Rovman Powell also made significant contributions. Hetmyer hit the top-gear at 194.44 straike rate, the highest since his 2019 IPL debut.
title: RR vs MI: Mumbai Indians gear up to face nemesis Buttler

description: Ongoing construction of Noida International Airport symbolizes rapid development and infrastructure growth, impacting surrounding areas. The project faces challenges related to land acquisition, compensation rates, and community welfare amidst promises and opposition concerns over local interests.
title: Airport nearly done, Jewar worries about jobs

description: Mumbai witnessed a significant 55%+ voter turnout in the latest general election, the highest since 1989. This increase is noteworthy despite challenges like the post-liberalisation era, heat, and a long weekend, with Mumbai South showing historically low participation rates.
title: Home to city’s richest, Mumbai South traditionally poor voter

description: A man pushed off a hotel terrace in Bareilly after an argument, leaving Sarthak Agrawal critically injured. Alcohol was involved in the incident, leading to grievous harm.
title: Drunk UP businessman pushes man off terrace at 5-star hotel

description: Kohli was dismissed by a waist-high full-toss, which he believed to be a no-ball as he maneuvered to avoid it hitting his body, but it resulted in an edge looping back to the bowler, Harshit Rana, who successfully took the catch. Chasing a stiff 223 to win, RCB lost the match by a mere one run to stay at rock bottom of the IPL 2024 points table.
title: Watch: Virat smashes trash can after controversial dismissal

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad opener Travis Head embraced Abhishek Sharma during their 100-run opening partnership at Arun Jaitley Stadium. Sharma's unabashed T20 batting this season, adding depth to their story. Head's impressive batwork has dominated IPL headlines, while Sharma's batting has earned him 257 runs.
title: With Head by his side & a clear mind, Abhishek is thriving

description: Gurgaon faced a devastating tragedy as a crematorium wall collapsed, impacting multiple families. The incident led to heartbreaking losses and highlighted the struggles faced by the victims and their loved ones.
title: Gurgaon families lose youngest & oldest in wall collapse

description: Machilakath Abdul Rahim's salvation from a death sentence in Saudi Arabia through a Rs 34 crore crowdfunding initiative during Ramzan and Vishu showcases the power of unity and compassion.
title: Hindus, Muslims join hands to help Indian on death row in Saudi

description: Rajkummar Rao denies plastic surgery rumors sparked by viral photos, dismissing them as a prank. In an interview, he humorously remarked that the images hardly resembled him. Admitting to receiving fillers years ago, he emphasized personal confidence. Meanwhile, Rao gears up for his film 'Srikanth,' showcasing his dedication to impactful performances.
title: Rajkummar Rao denies plastic surgery speculations, calls photos a prank

description: Ghazipur landfill fire required nine fire tenders for control, caused by methane production. AAP criticized for missed landfill deadlines. Arvind Kejriwal's absence during fire incident led to accusations of negligence. Deputy mayor Aaley Iqbal inspected the site.
title: Red hot Ghazipur: Delhi's mountain of shame up in flames, again

description: The 17-year-old Indian Grandmaster Gukesh scored 9/14 points to clinch the first place. He is only the the second Indian player after Viswanathan Anand to win the FIDE Candidates Tournament. The feat earns the teenager the right to challenge the reigning chess world champion Ding Liren. Praggnanandhaa finished fifth in the final standings.
title: Chess: Gukesh makes history as youngest to win Candidates

description: As Canadian college graduates lose post-graduation work permit eligibility, 10,000 Gujarat students are impacted. They often work to pay education loans. IRCC allocates permit quotas, emphasizing STEM and medical courses for better chances.
title: Canada dreams to be distant for many students

description: Hyderabad experiences a significant surge in water tanker demand due to water scarcity and IMD's heatwave prediction. Areas like S R Nagar witness high bookings, while the IT corridor receives increased water supply to address the rising demand.
title: Burst of demand for water board tankers in dehydrated Hyderabad

description: Sunil Mittal advocates for three private telecom operators in India, emphasizing Vi's financial lifeline and 5G rollout plans. Despite the capital infusion, analysts foresee challenges ahead for the telecom sector.
title: This is what Airtel chairman Mittal has to say on Voda-Idea raising funds

description: Rajan is currently lodged in a high-security cell in Jail No. 2 of Tihar Jail. While this photograph dispels rumours of his death during Covid pandemic or of ill-health, its release at this stage has also rekindled fears of an attack on him in jail, leaving the intelligence agencies alarmed.
title: 9 yrs after arrest, first pic of Chhota Rajan from Tihar is out

description: On Monday, Google released a new Doodle in celebration of Earth Day. The Doodle, replacing the iconic "Google" logo on the search engine's homepage, showcases aerial photographs of Earth, spotlighting areas where advancements have been achieved toward a more sustainable future. The Google letters highlight various locations of the Earth's natural beauty, biodiversity, and resources.
title: Earth Day: Google doodle celebrates with aerial photos
Brazilians laud Elon Musk at rally in support of ex-prez Bolsonaro

description: Apart from the gripping last-ball showdown witnessed during Sunday evening's IPL  match between the Kolkata Knight Riders and Royal Challengers Bengaluru at the Eden Gardens in Kolkata, the contentious dismissal of Virat Kohli on a waist-high delivery that was ruled legitimate stands out as a notable talking point from the encounter.
title: Out or not out? Experts weigh in on Kohli's dismissal

description: US President Joe Biden and First Lady Jill Biden conveyed their greetings to the Jain community on Mahavir Jayanti. In a post on X, Biden stated, "Jill and I wish a joyous Mahavir Jayanti to people of the Jain faith. Today, let us continue to recognize the values Mahavir Swami embodied and celebrate by spreading love, joy, and harmony."
title: Joe Biden, First lady Jill Biden extend greetings on Mahavir Jayanti
First time in 77 years, polling booth will come to Burudmal
Powered by brand PM Modi and RLD tie-up, Hema Malini in lead role again
AC, fridge & ice cream fly off shelves as summer heat bites
